# Data Professional Survey Dashboard (Power BI)

## Project Overview

This project analyzes a real survey dataset from data professionals around the world. The goal of this dashboard is to explore insights about salaries, job roles, programming languages, work-life balance, and the difficulty of entering the data industry.

The dashboard was built using **Power BI** with data cleaning performed in **Power Query**.

## Dataset

The dataset contains responses from **630 data professionals** including information such as:

* Job title
* Country
* Salary
* Programming language preference
* Age
* Work-life balance satisfaction
* Salary satisfaction
* Difficulty of breaking into the data field
* many more

## Data Cleaning

Before building the dashboard, several data preparation steps were performed:

* Cleaned column names and structured fields
* Handled categorical survey responses
* Organized job titles and programming language categories
* Prepared fields for visualization and analysis

Data transformations were performed using **Power Query**.

## Dashboard Insights

Key insights from the analysis include:

* Data Scientists have the highest average salary among surveyed roles.
* Python is the most popular programming language among data professionals.
* A large portion of respondents reported that breaking into the data field is **neither easy nor difficult**, with many still finding it challenging.
* The average age of survey participants is approximately **30 years old**.
* Work-life balance satisfaction is moderate, while salary satisfaction is slightly lower.

## Tools Used

* Power BI
* Power Query
* DAX (basic measures and aggregations)

